titleInfo.title: USA v. Bogenreif et al
titleInfo.subTitle: ORDER granting 20 Defendant Bogenreif's Motion to Extend Time. The deadline for filing pretrialmotions will be extended as to co-defendant Denice M Niedziela also. Defendants are given until on or before June 17, 2005, in which to file pretrial motions pursuantto the progression order 15. The time between May 19, 2005 and June17, 2005, shall be deemed excludable time in any computation of time under the requirement ofthe Speedy Trial Act. The tentative setting of an evidentiary hearing for 1:30 p.m. on May 27, 2005, iscanceled and will be re-scheduled in the event any pretrial motions are filed in accordance with thisorder. Signed by Magistrate Judge Thomas D. Thalken on 5/19/2005. (JAE, )

titleInfo.title: USA v. Bogenreif et al
titleInfo.subTitle: JUDGMENT as to Denice M. Niedziela (2): Defendant pleaded guilty to Count I of the Indictment and is committed to the custody of the Bureau of Prisons for a term of 41 months; 5 years supervised release with special conditions; $100 special assessment. The defendant shall surrender for service of sentence at the institution designated by the Bureau of Prisons on or after January 4, 2006. Counts IV, V, VI, VII of the Indictment are dismissed on the motion of the United States as to this defendant only, as to defendant Denice M. Niedziela. Signed by Judge Joseph F. Bataillon on 12/19/2005. 4 certified copies USM (JAE, )
